<TITLE> Quarishi accuses US of trying to make CHT a 'Christian land' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 13 (bdnews24.com)  Progressive Democratic Party chairman Ferdous Ahmed Quarishi has accused the United States of planning to establish a Christian-state in the Chittagong Hill Tracts by converting the Buddhists to Christianity. He also said that the decision to withdraw army and Bengali settlers from the region CHT was an act of sedition. "Few countries including the USA is dreaming of establishing a Christian-state in the Chittagong Hill Tracts. They are trying to convert the Buddhists to Christianity by operating Christian Missions there. They have gained some success in their effort over the last few years," said Quarishi in a press briefing in the capital on Saturday. "If this continues we might lose control of the area of the region within 20 to 30 years," he added. In response to the decision to pull the army out of the hills, he said, "the act is seditious under the constitution. The number of current troops level there is also inadequate." b
